### RULED_OUT
- Not T2/T3/T4 re-derivation: peck’s reviewer pass/fail loop is already represented as positive verification discipline in spec-kit’s completion and constitutional rules, but the freshness binding is missing. peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/implementer.md:38`; spec-kit: `CLAUDE.md:249`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/verify-before-completion-claims.md:30`.
- `session_dedup.fingerprint` is not already shipped as verdict freshness because current validation accepts a well-formed `sha256:<64-hex>` value rather than recomputing it against current scoped files. spec-kit: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/validation/spec-doc-structure.ts:636`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/validation/spec-doc-structure.ts:640`.
- `POST_SAVE_FINGERPRINT` is not completion freshness because it requires `postSavePlan` and otherwise reports “fingerprint check skipped.” spec-kit: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/validation/spec-doc-structure.ts:1072`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/validation/spec-doc-structure.ts:1077`.

